e current build now uses the sanitized `quarkus-junit` jar and avoids `quarkus-junit-config`, this exclusion should prevent the native-image heap error without reintroducing that JVM startup failure.\\n\\nI did not run the test command locally.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0a94b83a47d33d55016a277299ef488194b70790144c49b8ed\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 763, \"output\": 332, \"cacheRead\": 127488, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 128583, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1780970131273, \"responseId\": \"resp_0a94b83a47d33d55016a277294b1f081949eeecd8df76785f2\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n[recv] agent_end\n[send] get_state\n[recv] {\"type\": \"compaction_start\", \"reason\": \"overflow\"}\n[recv] get_state success\n  sessionFile: ../../../../../../../../.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge-forge1-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-3611-2dea1afc--/2026-06-09T01-34-43-990Z_019eaa04-8716-75d4-9899-51b8d8ee6748.jsonl\n  sessionId: 019eaa04-8716-75d4-9899-51b8d8ee6748\n[send] get_session_stats\n[recv] get_session_stats success\n  tokens: input=194240 output=13892 cacheRead=3446272 cacheWrite=0 total=3654404\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
