access coverage is unavailable because `stats/io.quarkus/quarkus-junit/3.33.1/stats.json` was never produced.\n\nPlease inspect `logs/io.quarkus:quarkus-junit:3.33.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-09T01-39-29-098544Z.log`, `logs/io.quarkus:quarkus-junit:3.33.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-09T01-54-49-327471Z.log`, `logs/io.quarkus:quarkus-junit:3.33.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-09T01-43-27-063009Z.log`, and `tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-junit/3.33.1/build/native/nativeTestCompile/svm_err_b_20260609T035458.736_pid3206293.md`.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Rework the generated `quarkus-junit` test module so it removes the scaffold placeholder and avoids the JBoss LogManager / SmallRye runtime-initialization objects currently breaking `nativeTestCompile`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.quarkus:quarkus-junit:3.33.1` on the preserved branch and verify both the earlier classpath issue (`guice-5.1.0-classes.jar`) and the native-image build.\n3. If native-image cannot be made green for this artifact, decide whether `io.quarkus:quarkus-junit` is a poor new-library target compared with `io.quarkus:quarkus-junit-common`, and document that outcome on the issue."}}
